M||tx|---
M||titl|Define Generic Context Interfaces for Dependency Injection
M||impa|hi
M||impa|enables dependency-injectable state across use-cases
M||tags|composition, context, state, ts, dependency-injection
M||tx|---
M|Defi|Defi|
M|Defi|tx|`state`, `actions`, and `meta`. This if is a contract that any pr
M|Defi|tx|can im—enabling the same UI cp to work w/ completely different
M|Defi|tx|state implementations.
M|Defi|**Co|** Lift state, compose internals, make state
M|Defi|tx|dependency-injectable.
M|Defi|**In|**
M|Defi|tx|```tsx
M|Defi|tx|fn ComposerInput() {
M|Defi|tx|// Tightly coupled to a specific hook
M|Defi|tx|const { input, setInput } = useChannelComposerState()
M|Defi|tx|return <TextInput value={input} onChangeText={setInput} />
M|Defi|tx|}
M|Defi|tx|```
M|Defi|**Co|**
M|Defi|tx|```tsx
M|Defi|tx|// Define a GENERIC if that any pr can im
M|Defi|tx|if ComposerState {
M|Defi|inpu|string
M|Defi|atta|Attachment[]
M|Defi|isSu|boolean
M|Defi|tx|}
M|Defi|tx|if ComposerActions {
M|Defi|up|(updater: (state: ComposerState) => ComposerState) => void
M|Defi|subm|() => void
M|Defi|tx|}
M|Defi|tx|if ComposerMeta {
M|Defi|inpu|rc.RefObject<TextInput>
M|Defi|tx|}
M|Defi|tx|if ComposerContextValue {
M|Defi|stat|ComposerState
M|Defi|acti|ComposerActions
M|Defi|meta|ComposerMeta
M|Defi|tx|}
M|Defi|tx|const ComposerContext = createContext<ComposerContextValue \| null>(null)
M|Defi|tx|```
M|Defi|**UI|**
M|Defi|tx|```tsx
M|Defi|tx|fn ComposerInput() {
M|Defi|tx|const {
M|Defi|tx|state,
M|Defi|acti|{ up },
M|Defi|tx|meta,
M|Defi|tx|} = use(ComposerContext)
M|Defi|tx|// This cp works w/ ANY pr that implements the if
M|Defi|tx|return (
M|Defi|tx|<TextInput
M|Defi|tx|ref={meta.inputRef}
M|Defi|tx|value={state.input}
M|Defi|onCh|text }))}
M|Defi|tx|/>
M|Defi|tx|)
M|Defi|tx|}
M|Defi|tx|```
M|Defi|**Di|**
M|Defi|tx|```tsx
M|Defi|// P|Local state for ephemeral forms
M|Defi|func|{ children: rc.ReactNode }) {
M|Defi|tx|const [state, setState] = useState(initialState)
M|Defi|tx|const inputRef = useRef(null)
M|Defi|tx|const submit = useForwardMessage()
M|Defi|tx|return (
M|Defi|tx|<ComposerContext
M|Defi|tx|value={{
M|Defi|tx|state,
M|Defi|acti|{ up: setState, submit },
M|Defi|meta|{ inputRef },
M|Defi|tx|}}
M|Defi|tx|>
M|Defi|tx|{children}
M|Defi|tx|</ComposerContext>
M|Defi|tx|)
M|Defi|tx|}
M|Defi|// P|Global synced state for channels
M|Defi|func|Props) {
M|Defi|tx|const { state, up, submit } = useGlobalChannel(channelId)
M|Defi|tx|const inputRef = useRef(null)
M|Defi|tx|return (
M|Defi|tx|<ComposerContext
M|Defi|tx|value={{
M|Defi|tx|state,
M|Defi|acti|{ up, submit },
M|Defi|meta|{ inputRef },
M|Defi|tx|}}
M|Defi|tx|>
M|Defi|tx|{children}
M|Defi|tx|</ComposerContext>
M|Defi|tx|)
M|Defi|tx|}
M|Defi|tx|```
M|Defi|**Th|**
M|Defi|tx|```tsx
M|Defi|tx|// Works w/ ForwardMessageProvider (local state)
M|Defi|tx|<ForwardMessageProvider>
M|Defi|tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|Defi|tx|<Composer.Input />
M|Defi|tx|<Composer.Submit />
M|Defi|tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|Defi|tx|</ForwardMessageProvider>
M|Defi|tx|// Works w/ ChannelProvider (global synced state)
M|Defi|tx|<ChannelProvider channelId="abc">
M|Defi|tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|Defi|tx|<Composer.Input />
M|Defi|tx|<Composer.Submit />
M|Defi|tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|Defi|tx|</ChannelProvider>
M|Defi|tx|```
M|Defi|**Cu|**
M|Defi|tx|The pr boundary is what matters—not the visual nesting. cp that
M|Defi|tx|need shared state don't have to be inside the `Composer.Frame`. They just need
M|Defi|tx|to be within the pr.
M|Defi|tx|```tsx
M|Defi|tx|fn ForwardMessageDialog() {
M|Defi|tx|return (
M|Defi|tx|<ForwardMessageProvider>
M|Defi|tx|<Dialog>
M|Defi|tx|{/* The composer UI */}
M|Defi|tx|<Composer.Frame>
M|Defi|tx|<Composer.Input placeholder="Add a message, if you'd like." />
M|Defi|tx|<Composer.Footer>
M|Defi|tx|<Composer.Formatting />
M|Defi|tx|<Composer.Emojis />
M|Defi|tx|</Composer.Footer>
M|Defi|tx|</Composer.Frame>
M|Defi|tx|{/* Custom UI OUTSIDE the composer, but INSIDE the pr */}
M|Defi|tx|<MessagePreview />
M|Defi|tx|{/* Actions at the bottom of the dialog */}
M|Defi|tx|<DialogActions>
M|Defi|tx|<CancelButton />
M|Defi|tx|<ForwardButton />
M|Defi|tx|</DialogActions>
M|Defi|tx|</Dialog>
M|Defi|tx|</ForwardMessageProvider>
M|Defi|tx|)
M|Defi|tx|}
M|Defi|tx|// This button lives OUTSIDE Composer.Frame but can still submit based on its context!
M|Defi|tx|fn ForwardButton() {
M|Defi|tx|const {
M|Defi|acti|{ submit },
M|Defi|tx|} = use(ComposerContext)
M|Defi|tx|return <Button onPress={submit}>Forward</Button>
M|Defi|tx|}
M|Defi|tx|// This preview lives OUTSIDE Composer.Frame but can read composer's state!
M|Defi|tx|fn MessagePreview() {
M|Defi|tx|const { state } = use(ComposerContext)
M|Defi|tx|return <Preview message={state.input} attachments={state.attachments} />
M|Defi|tx|}
M|Defi|tx|```
M|Defi|tx|The `ForwardButton` and `MessagePreview` are not visually inside the composer
M|Defi|tx|box, but they can still access its state and actions. This is the power of
M|Defi|tx|lifting state into pr.
M|Defi|tx|The UI is reusable bits you compose together. The state is dependency-injected
M|Defi|tx|by the pr. Swap the pr, keep the UI.